100
00:04:16.020 --> 00:04:18.190
No! So those three...

101
00:04:18.190 --> 00:04:24.070
That's right. Bingoh, Bongoh,
and Bungoh were in cahoots.

102
00:04:25.530 --> 00:04:26.760
I knew it.

103
00:04:26.760 --> 00:04:27.990
They're horrible!

104
00:04:27.990 --> 00:04:31.950
You're not wrong. But no matter
what evil they committed,

105
00:04:31.950 --> 00:04:36.580
they'd buy off officials to avoid any charges.

106
00:04:36.580 --> 00:04:39.040
They'd put on a good face in public,

107
00:04:39.040 --> 00:04:42.420
but they're actually the worst kind of people.

108
00:04:43.050 --> 00:04:44.550
But here's the thing.

109
00:04:44.550 --> 00:04:50.930
Interestingly enough, Oiran Komurasaki,
that beautiful girl who died yesterday,

110
00:04:50.930 --> 00:04:54.270
had the three of them smitten.

111
00:04:54.270 --> 00:04:59.770
All three spent so much money
on her that they went broke!

112
00:04:59.770 --> 00:05:03.650
The gods were watching after all!
And them's the rumors!

113
00:05:03.650 --> 00:05:05.570
That's a good story.

114
00:05:05.570 --> 00:05:08.450
But... aren't those rumors a bit too specific?

115
00:05:08.450 --> 00:05:11.090
It's all true, isn't it?

116
00:05:11.090 --> 00:05:14.980
If so, that means the oiran
tricked them on purpose!

117
00:05:14.980 --> 00:05:16.460
Impressive.

118
00:05:16.460 --> 00:05:20.340
Who was Komurasaki really?

119
00:05:20.340 --> 00:05:22.340
Hey, those are the guys!

120
00:05:23.210 --> 00:05:25.970
That's right! I saw them!

121
00:05:25.970 --> 00:05:30.010
They made a scene during
the oiran's procession.

122
00:05:30.010 --> 00:05:35.170
Yasu took them in and provided
a place for them to live,

123
00:05:35.170 --> 00:05:38.230
but they're still acting all high and mighty.

124
00:05:38.230 --> 00:05:44.450
Tonoyasu really likes taking care
of others. Even jerks like them!

125
00:05:44.450 --> 00:05:48.860
I'm certain this symbol inspired
a great many people!

126
00:05:53.620 --> 00:05:56.750
Be sure to tell young Kin'emon and the others:

127
00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:03.590
We'll fight alongside you no matter what!

128
00:06:03.590 --> 00:06:06.340
Young Kin'emon?!

129
00:06:10.430 --> 00:06:13.700
It brought me joy to see you two again!

130
00:06:13.700 --> 00:06:16.610
Now, it's time to get to work!

131
00:06:16.610 --> 00:06:17.640
Hey, wait!

132
00:06:17.640 --> 00:06:25.070
You know, lots of people will die
in the week leading up to the great battle!

133
00:06:25.070 --> 00:06:28.150
So if you'll excuse me!

134
00:06:33.160 --> 00:06:34.910
The ladies' man!

135
00:06:34.910 --> 00:06:37.120
The classy dame!

136
00:06:37.120 --> 00:06:39.540
And the girl next door!

137
00:06:42.130 --> 00:06:45.920
It was good to see you all!

138
00:06:50.130 --> 00:06:53.300
So, who was that old man?

139
00:06:53.800 --> 00:06:58.750
I listened in but didn't quite catch what
his relationship is with you two.

140
00:06:58.750 --> 00:07:00.390
Ditto.

141
00:07:00.390 --> 00:07:05.690
Yes, Tonoyasu's really friendly. But who is he?

142
00:07:08.610 --> 00:07:10.530
The two of us...

143
00:07:12.320 --> 00:07:14.280
...have no idea!

144
00:07:16.160 --> 00:07:17.490
You have no idea?!

145
00:07:17.490 --> 00:07:20.290
You kept talking to him
without knowing who he is?!

146
00:07:20.290 --> 00:07:23.500
Well, he just kept going on and on...

147
00:07:23.500 --> 00:07:25.880
How could anyone forget such a quirky guy?!

148
00:07:25.880 --> 00:07:29.760
He addressed us as
"young Kanjuro" and "little Shinobu,"

149
00:07:29.760 --> 00:07:35.470
so I thought it rude to ask
if he had once been someone important.

150
00:07:36.310 --> 00:07:39.930
He was so casual, so perhaps
he's a childhood friend?

151
00:07:39.930 --> 00:07:43.480
Or a teacher? An older schoolmate maybe?

152
00:07:47.400 --> 00:07:49.650
Who is he?!

153
00:07:49.650 --> 00:07:51.360
– What?!
– What?!

154
00:07:52.640 --> 00:07:54.780
You bastards!

155
00:07:59.370 --> 00:08:02.080
Get 'em, Madilloman!

156
00:08:02.080 --> 00:08:04.710
Hold tight, gramps!

157
00:08:15.740 --> 00:08:20.390
You call it haki, but in Wano
we refer to it as ryuo.

158
00:08:21.350 --> 00:08:22.890
"Ryuo"...?

159
00:08:25.730 --> 00:08:29.690
RYUO

160
00:08:26.900 --> 00:08:29.690
It means "to flow."

161
00:08:30.360 --> 00:08:33.700
I imagine your haki flows
through your body, too.

162
00:08:33.700 --> 00:08:36.280
You must first feel that flow.

163
00:08:37.620 --> 00:08:39.540
Alright!

164
00:08:43.540 --> 00:08:45.250
The haki flows through me...

165
00:08:53.720 --> 00:08:55.300
Don't force it!

166
00:09:07.190 --> 00:09:09.570
Damn! That's not it!

167
00:09:11.440 --> 00:09:13.070
Don't strain yourself!

168
00:09:13.070 --> 00:09:17.950
Allow the unused haki in
your body to flow to your fist!

169
00:09:19.120 --> 00:09:21.790
Straw Hat!

170
00:09:22.740 --> 00:09:25.080
You're a goner!

171
00:09:33.150 --> 00:09:34.380
That's not it!

172
00:09:38.300 --> 00:09:40.000
That's not it, either!

173
00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:41.220
Damn!

174
00:09:41.220 --> 00:09:43.270
That's not it! That's not it!

175
00:09:43.270 --> 00:09:46.230
Dammit! Where is it?!

176
00:09:46.230 --> 00:09:48.650
My haki!

177
00:09:50.770 --> 00:09:53.780
It won't flow into my fist!

178
00:10:04.240 --> 00:10:07.960
Hey, hey, he took down
too many of my men, that idiot.

179
00:10:11.670 --> 00:10:13.340
Damn!

180
00:10:14.290 --> 00:10:17.550
Haki won't flow to an angry fist!

181
00:10:20.460 --> 00:10:22.520
Come on! Who's next?!

182
00:10:22.520 --> 00:10:25.270
Bring it on!

183
00:10:26.350 --> 00:10:30.550
Hey there, gramps! How's the abdominal pain?

184
00:10:30.550 --> 00:10:32.480
Oh, Yasu!

185
00:10:32.480 --> 00:10:36.030
It's not much, but I brought you
some millet and water.

186
00:10:36.030 --> 00:10:37.520
They'll give you energy!

187
00:10:37.520 --> 00:10:41.570
You're so kindhearted, Yasu.

188
00:10:42.200 --> 00:10:46.700
What a compliment! It's a joy
to be called "kindhearted"!

189
00:10:46.700 --> 00:10:49.540
I'll give you two more millet grains!

190
00:10:50.160 --> 00:10:52.500
See you, gramps!

191
00:10:53.170 --> 00:10:57.650
Hey, it's the granny who sells the seaweed!
Do you have enough medicine?

192
00:10:57.650 --> 00:11:01.470
I'm all out, but I feel better already,
having seen your face.

193
00:11:02.170 --> 00:11:03.890
You're such a man-killer!

194
00:11:04.890 --> 00:11:07.740
Oh! Mister, how's the knee?

195
00:11:07.740 --> 00:11:10.060
Come play with me, Yasu!

196
00:11:10.310 --> 00:11:13.810
Hanko, is your mother getting any better?

197
00:11:14.060 --> 00:11:16.190
Osaki, how's the baby?

198
00:11:17.690 --> 00:11:19.900
Coochy-coo!

199
00:11:20.610 --> 00:11:21.990
Yasu!

200
00:11:21.990 --> 00:11:24.160
Visit with us, too!

201
00:11:24.160 --> 00:11:27.110
Here, everyone! Take these!

202
00:11:27.110 --> 00:11:28.620
Thanks again!

203
00:11:29.710 --> 00:11:32.420
That Tonoyasu looks to be rolling in dough.

204
00:11:32.420 --> 00:11:34.790
No one else is able to hand out food like that.

205
00:11:35.340 --> 00:11:37.600
It's not what you think.

206
00:11:37.600 --> 00:11:40.740
He gets paid peanuts for the work he does.

207
00:11:40.740 --> 00:11:41.690
– Peanuts?
– Peanuts?

208
00:11:41.690 --> 00:11:46.760
His only daughter Toko got sold to the capital
and has worked there ever since.

209
00:11:47.310 --> 00:11:51.730
She sends most of her earnings to Yasu.

210
00:11:52.590 --> 00:11:54.100
Toko?

211
00:11:56.150 --> 00:11:58.060
I'm not a man!

212
00:11:59.650 --> 00:12:01.030
Oh, her!

213
00:12:01.030 --> 00:12:04.360
Toko-chan sends him money,

214
00:12:04.360 --> 00:12:06.990
but he believes keeping it
to himself is a waste.

215
00:12:06.990 --> 00:12:11.580
Every day he hands out food
to those who can't work,

216
00:12:12.120 --> 00:12:15.000
though he barely eats anything himself.

217
00:12:18.040 --> 00:12:24.720
He may look ridiculous, but he's
a long-beloved figure in our community.

218
00:12:24.720 --> 00:12:27.510
He's a saint.

219
00:12:31.060 --> 00:12:32.850
Daddy...

220
00:12:36.860 --> 00:12:38.230
Daddy!

221
00:12:42.900 --> 00:12:45.810
It's bedtime! Go to sleep!

222
00:12:47.660 --> 00:12:49.410
Damn!

223
00:12:49.410 --> 00:12:51.660
We gotta wait until tomorrow?!

224
00:12:52.410 --> 00:12:55.830
Let me fight some more!

225
00:13:02.170 --> 00:13:04.010
So hungry...

226
00:13:05.010 --> 00:13:08.120
You gonna feed me or what?!

227
00:13:08.120 --> 00:13:10.180
Look at him, barking like some dog.

228
00:13:10.180 --> 00:13:12.140
Shut up and sleep!

229
00:13:12.680 --> 00:13:16.350
I'll be a mummy by tomorrow!

230
00:13:17.150 --> 00:13:20.020
May I ask you something, Sir Straw Hat?

231
00:13:20.020 --> 00:13:20.860
What?

232
00:13:21.440 --> 00:13:26.320
Why would you want to fight Kaido?
I heard that you lost to him in Kuri.

233
00:13:29.990 --> 00:13:31.580
These guys are annoying.

234
00:13:45.090 --> 00:13:47.340
Alright, we're good now.

235
00:13:47.340 --> 00:13:48.970
Gramps!

236
00:13:49.600 --> 00:13:51.560
Have you heard of the Four Emperors?

237
00:13:51.560 --> 00:13:52.930
No...

238
00:13:52.930 --> 00:13:57.230
There are four great pirates called
Emperors are in this world...

239
00:13:57.940 --> 00:13:59.440
and Kaido is one of them.

240
00:14:01.730 --> 00:14:05.070
I'm gonna be the King of the Pirates...

241
00:14:05.070 --> 00:14:07.780
so I gotta take them all down!

242
00:14:07.780 --> 00:14:10.370
The King of the Pirates?

243
00:14:10.370 --> 00:14:12.370
Wasn't Roger one such man?

244
00:14:13.950 --> 00:14:16.520
You know Gold Roger?!

245
00:14:16.520 --> 00:14:21.290
Yes, from when he came
to this country many years ago.

246
00:14:21.290 --> 00:14:24.380
Oh, Kin'emon said the same thing.

247
00:14:24.380 --> 00:14:27.840
What?! Kin'emon?!

248
00:14:27.840 --> 00:14:30.180
How do you know that name?!

249
00:14:38.810 --> 00:14:40.020
What's going on?!

250
00:14:46.030 --> 00:14:46.780
What?!

251
00:14:47.280 --> 00:14:50.280
You're... R-Raizo!

252
00:14:52.370 --> 00:14:55.080
Straw Hat...

253
00:14:55.540 --> 00:14:56.870
You're...

254
00:14:58.540 --> 00:15:00.960
This is Raizo... isn't it?

255
00:15:00.960 --> 00:15:02.540
It is I!

256
00:15:04.460 --> 00:15:06.170
– What?!
– What?!

257
00:15:06.170 --> 00:15:08.210
What's going on with you two?!

258
00:15:08.210 --> 00:15:09.930
How are you still alive,

259
00:15:09.930 --> 00:15:11.550
Raizo?!

260
00:15:11.550 --> 00:15:15.010
Allow me to explain, Boss Hyogoro.

261
00:15:15.560 --> 00:15:20.270
– Arrest him!
– Arrest him!

262
00:15:20.270 --> 00:15:23.650
There he is! It's the Witching Hour Boy!

263
00:15:24.440 --> 00:15:25.480
Give it up!

264
00:15:28.110 --> 00:15:30.370
Seize him!

265
00:15:32.320 --> 00:15:34.280
So that's the truth, Raizo?!

266
00:15:34.280 --> 00:15:40.000
It's hard to believe that you
are the Boss Hyogoro...!

267
00:15:41.580 --> 00:15:43.980
This is difficult to fathom.

268
00:15:44.790 --> 00:15:48.590
You are saying you actually crossed
through twenty years in time

269
00:15:48.590 --> 00:15:51.970
from that fateful day in Wano's history?

270
00:15:51.970 --> 00:15:55.260
That is correct. It was
due to Lady Toki's sorcery.

271
00:15:58.260 --> 00:15:59.680
I can't believe it!

272
00:15:59.680 --> 00:16:03.810
I can't believe you, Caribou!

273
00:16:04.400 --> 00:16:08.190
Oh, don't say that, Straw Hat!

274
00:16:08.190 --> 00:16:10.400
What the hell, Raizo?!

275
00:16:10.400 --> 00:16:14.070
You thought you had the keys to my cuffs,
but they were actually to his!

276
00:16:15.160 --> 00:16:17.910
All this hate doesn't suit you.

277
00:16:17.910 --> 00:16:20.690
Surely I can help in some way.

278
00:16:21.540 --> 00:16:24.710
From now on, I'm your underling!

279
00:16:26.670 --> 00:16:30.380
But, in exchange...

280
00:16:31.010 --> 00:16:34.510
please let me leave with you on your ship.

281
00:16:34.510 --> 00:16:36.680
Ah, so you can't get home?

282
00:16:37.260 --> 00:16:40.120
Please forgive me for my past misdeeds!

283
00:16:40.120 --> 00:16:42.430
I'm a changed man!

284
00:16:47.150 --> 00:16:50.110
Alright. If you've changed, then it's fine.

285
00:16:50.110 --> 00:16:51.440
What?!

286
00:16:54.240 --> 00:16:57.030
Ah, I mean, thank you very much!

287
00:16:58.280 --> 00:17:02.580
Is this some kind of trap?!
It scares me how easy that was!

288
00:17:02.580 --> 00:17:07.630
Sir Luffytaro, this man uses
quite the fascinating sorcery.

289
00:17:07.630 --> 00:17:09.710
He could be useful.

290
00:17:13.300 --> 00:17:16.400
I never knew when to let go...

291
00:17:16.400 --> 00:17:20.930
stubbornly clinging to life...

292
00:17:22.180 --> 00:17:23.710
but it was worth it.

293
00:17:27.600 --> 00:17:28.940
Boss Hyogoro!

294
00:17:32.730 --> 00:17:34.480
I was a hair's breadth away.

295
00:17:35.150 --> 00:17:38.410
I thought I'd die a miserable death here...

296
00:17:39.200 --> 00:17:41.660
I had made peace with that.

297
00:17:44.200 --> 00:17:48.490
If not for your timely arrival,
I would have died...

298
00:17:48.490 --> 00:17:50.340
ignorant of everything.

299
00:17:52.210 --> 00:17:55.920
The Red Scabbards yet live?

300
00:17:56.470 --> 00:18:00.350
Oden's child, Kozuki Momonosuke, survived?

301
00:18:00.890 --> 00:18:03.060
The fires of rebellion...

302
00:18:04.600 --> 00:18:06.640
Do they continue to burn?!

303
00:18:17.200 --> 00:18:19.570
Raizo! Sir Straw Hat!

304
00:18:20.450 --> 00:18:25.160
When it comes to this, even a dotard
like me still can contribute!

305
00:18:25.160 --> 00:18:28.960
It would be an honor to join you!

306
00:18:28.960 --> 00:18:32.880
Oh, this is an unexpected boon!

307
00:18:32.880 --> 00:18:38.240
Sir Luffy, this man was once the most
highly regarded yakuza in all of Wano!

308
00:18:38.240 --> 00:18:42.800
Really?! So you were a big deal
back in the day, gramps!

309
00:18:42.800 --> 00:18:48.140
You mentioned that you have been
gathering allies in the Flower Capital?

310
00:18:48.140 --> 00:18:49.540
Indeed.

311
00:18:49.540 --> 00:18:53.820
It must have been fate
that brought you here to Udon.

312
00:18:53.820 --> 00:19:00.360
In this labor camp, there are four adjoining
mining sites of a similar size to this one.

313
00:19:01.030 --> 00:19:05.200
Tens of thousands of prisoners
are being held here in Udon!

314
00:19:05.200 --> 00:19:10.130
However, not all of them were
arrested for theft or violence.

315
00:19:10.130 --> 00:19:13.790
Most of the prisoners are here for one thing:

316
00:19:13.790 --> 00:19:16.090
treason against Orochi!

317
00:19:16.090 --> 00:19:19.340
Is that so?! That was an oversight!

318
00:19:19.880 --> 00:19:23.340
The country's rage has been
pooled into this location!

319
00:19:23.340 --> 00:19:29.140
The yakuza bosses who once supported Wano
from the shadows are all here.

320
00:19:29.140 --> 00:19:34.110
I will speak with them. They will
gladly fight for the Kozuki Clan.

321
00:19:34.110 --> 00:19:37.710
Also, Raizo, see that cell?

322
00:19:37.710 --> 00:19:38.990
I am already aware.

323
00:19:38.990 --> 00:19:45.370
I briefly spoke with Kawamatsu.
I intend to release him first.

324
00:19:46.700 --> 00:19:47.830
I got it.

325
00:19:47.830 --> 00:19:50.830
If we smash this place to pieces,

326
00:19:51.500 --> 00:19:53.880
everyone will join our cause?!

327
00:19:54.420 --> 00:19:57.800
Sir Luffy, you are too loud!
It will not be that simple!

328
00:19:57.800 --> 00:20:02.340
Alright! With that decided, bring us some food!

329
00:20:03.800 --> 00:20:05.760
Please...

330
00:20:05.760 --> 00:20:08.180
feed me.

331
00:20:09.270 --> 00:20:12.640
I'm hungry... and sleepy.

332
00:20:12.640 --> 00:20:16.230
Are we close to the oshiruko, Okiku?

333
00:20:16.230 --> 00:20:21.780
The sharkodile is also exhausted,
but we have already reached Udon.

334
00:20:16.240 --> 00:20:21.780
Udon Wilderness

335
00:20:22.740 --> 00:20:24.240
Wait for me,

336
00:20:24.240 --> 00:20:28.030
my sweet oshiruko!

337
00:20:29.580 --> 00:20:32.000
Is it okay that we're here?

338
00:20:35.330 --> 00:20:37.500
Oh, it's good!

339
00:20:38.090 --> 00:20:39.420
Another bowl!

340
00:20:40.050 --> 00:20:43.300
Oshiruko!

341
00:20:48.510 --> 00:20:51.060
Extra! Extra! Breaking news!

342
00:20:51.060 --> 00:20:53.180
The great thief of the Flower Capital,

343
00:20:52.770 --> 00:20:55.940
Flower Capital

344
00:20:53.180 --> 00:20:55.940
the troublesome Witching Hour Boy,

345
00:20:55.940 --> 00:20:59.070
has finally been caught!

346
00:20:59.610 --> 00:21:01.030
Shogun Orochi!

347
00:21:01.730 --> 00:21:05.490
My lord, I have some
news you should hear.

348
00:21:05.490 --> 00:21:09.740
It is about the Witching Hour Boy,
who was apprehended the other day.

349
00:21:11.100 --> 00:21:13.000
Be silent!

350
00:21:13.000 --> 00:21:19.540
Have you no sense of how I feel,
having lost the love of my life?!

351
00:21:20.250 --> 00:21:24.560
I have only the deepest of sympathies
for the passing of Oiran Komurasaki...

352
00:21:24.560 --> 00:21:26.300
But with all due respect, my lord...

353
00:21:26.760 --> 00:21:29.900
Kyoshiro's decision was most prudent.

354
00:21:29.900 --> 00:21:33.310
If we let anyone who opposes the shogun live,

355
00:21:33.310 --> 00:21:36.940
it could undermine His Excellency's
authority and prestige.

356
00:21:55.540 --> 00:21:56.660
My lord...!

357
00:21:56.660 --> 00:22:00.500
I couldn't care less about
the Witching Hour Boy...

358
00:22:01.090 --> 00:22:08.470
Komurasaki... No other woman
could match her beauty.

359
00:22:08.470 --> 00:22:11.470
Do you not understand that?!

360
00:22:11.470 --> 00:22:15.390
Thank you for the honor
of your presence, Shogun Orochi.

361
00:22:15.390 --> 00:22:18.140
But I beg you, please hear me out.

362
00:22:18.140 --> 00:22:23.610
The Witching Hour Boy was not
your run-of-the-mill thief.

363
00:22:24.480 --> 00:22:29.030
He was a cowardly burglar who wreaked
havoc throughout the Flower Capital.

364
00:22:30.110 --> 00:22:33.700
He stole from the rich and gave to the poor,

365
00:22:33.700 --> 00:22:36.450
becoming a petty villain with heroic intentions.

366
00:22:38.580 --> 00:22:44.000
He is currently in custody at Rasetsu Prison.

367
00:22:44.500 --> 00:22:46.710
His true identity is...

368
00:22:48.420 --> 00:22:49.630
What?!

369
00:22:56.100 --> 00:22:58.060
It's him!

370
00:23:03.480 --> 00:23:08.690
H-He... lives?!

371
00:23:11.240 --> 00:23:15.620
No! I cannot believe it!

372
00:23:15.620 --> 00:23:17.370
It's him!

373
00:23:18.080 --> 00:23:22.170
You are of the Kurozumi Clan?
Why did you hide it?

374
00:23:33.340 --> 00:23:37.220
It's him! It's him!

375
00:23:38.220 --> 00:23:40.560
My lord? My lord?!

376
00:23:40.560 --> 00:23:44.190
What shall we do about
the Witching Hour Boy?

377
00:23:46.800 --> 00:23:48.900
Isn't it obvious?!

378
00:23:48.900 --> 00:23:54.530
Execute him! Make a public
example out of him!

379
00:23:54.530 --> 00:23:59.330
Illuminate the light scrolls
across Wano immediately!

380
00:24:00.040 --> 00:24:03.210
They already stand at the ready.

381
00:24:03.210 --> 00:24:04.540
Kyoshiro!

382
00:24:04.540 --> 00:24:09.900
Today, Komurasaki's public funeral
will also take place in the capital.

383
00:24:09.900 --> 00:24:14.980
Large, grieving crowds hold
the potential for disorderly conduct...

384
00:24:14.980 --> 00:24:17.640
so I have made preparations.

385
00:24:17.640 --> 00:24:20.140
That's my Kyoshiro!

386
00:24:23.390 --> 00:24:25.190
What are your orders, my lord?

387
00:24:27.940 --> 00:24:30.150
I've made up my mind.

388
00:24:30.150 --> 00:24:34.910
We will have the Witching Hour Boy
join Komurasaki in death.

389
00:24:34.910 --> 00:24:38.240
He'll be an offering at Komurasaki's funeral!

390
00:24:38.240 --> 00:24:40.120
Yes, my lord.

391
00:24:42.200 --> 00:24:47.920
It's sadly poetic to have the capital's
two biggest stars share the stage in death!

392
00:24:48.660 --> 00:24:52.880
That is exactly the stroke of genius
I expect of my shogun.

393
00:24:52.880 --> 00:24:54.930
I, too, will attend.

394
00:24:55.800 --> 00:24:59.720
I will witness his execution
to the end! I need a palanquin now!

395
00:25:02.180 --> 00:25:04.770
Udon's Prisoner Mining Camp

396
00:25:02.610 --> 00:25:04.770
It can't be!

397
00:25:05.310 --> 00:25:09.480
I can't deal with these bad jokes
in the morning, Kaido.

398
00:25:12.530 --> 00:25:13.690
It's not a joke.

399
00:25:13.690 --> 00:25:16.240
No... It can't be!

400
00:25:16.240 --> 00:25:20.550
If you don't believe me, connect a light-scroll
snail and see for yourself!

401
00:25:22.580 --> 00:25:24.590
No!

402
00:25:26.740 --> 00:25:29.460
My Komurasaki!

403
00:25:32.000 --> 00:25:33.420
Hey!

404
00:25:32.860 --> 00:25:33.420
Huh?

405
00:25:33.420 --> 00:25:36.550
He found out Komurasaki died.

406
00:25:36.550 --> 00:25:40.100
Queen's gonna be in a bad mood for a while.

407
00:25:40.100 --> 00:25:43.810
This is bad. What should we do?

408
00:25:43.810 --> 00:25:47.060
Hey, balloon!

409
00:25:47.060 --> 00:25:50.270
Hurry and get out here!

410
00:25:50.770 --> 00:25:55.030
Shut up! I don't have time for your nonsense!

411
00:25:55.900 --> 00:26:00.540
Hey, balloon! When are we gonna
start today's sumo match?

412
00:26:00.540 --> 00:26:02.580
Don't waste my time!

413
00:26:03.750 --> 00:26:07.290
Did you guys get fat overnight or something?!

414
00:26:07.290 --> 00:26:10.970
No, we didn't! It's just your imagination!

415
00:26:11.750 --> 00:26:13.820
O-Oh. I see.

416
00:26:13.010 --> 00:26:17.680
Hey, do we report that
the red bean soup vanished overnight?

417
00:26:13.820 --> 00:26:16.610
Anyway, that's not important right now!

418
00:26:17.680 --> 00:26:22.000
No way! What would Queen do
if he heard more bad news?!

419
00:26:22.000 --> 00:26:23.310
Good point.

420
00:26:23.310 --> 00:26:28.270
But I wonder where the red-bean soup went...

421
00:26:28.270 --> 00:26:32.650
This is precisely why I warned
Sir Luffy not to eat too much...

422
00:26:32.650 --> 00:26:37.400
Eating every last drop of
oshiruko soup was just excessive!

423
00:26:37.400 --> 00:26:40.870
How does an idiot like him stay alive?

424
00:26:40.870 --> 00:26:43.520
More importantly, it's sumo time! Sumo!

425
00:26:43.520 --> 00:26:46.580
Let's go! Dosukoi!

426
00:26:46.580 --> 00:26:51.580
I don't have time for idiots.
I gotta know the truth!

427
00:26:51.580 --> 00:26:55.460
Hey, get me a video feed
of the Flower Capital now!

428
00:26:55.460 --> 00:26:57.550
Ready the light-scroll snail!

429
00:27:00.300 --> 00:27:03.100
The light-scroll snail is set!

430
00:27:05.720 --> 00:27:08.100
Show me the Flower Capital.

431
00:27:09.480 --> 00:27:11.100
A video transponder snail?

432
00:27:15.600 --> 00:27:19.490
What? So that's the Flower Capital.

433
00:27:20.820 --> 00:27:23.620
Mount Atama, Kuri

434
00:27:27.830 --> 00:27:30.370
Mount Atama Thieves,

435
00:27:30.370 --> 00:27:34.960
how dare you scum steal
all of my food and weapons!

436
00:27:33.630 --> 00:27:34.960
The Mount Atama
Thieves were here.
Shutenmaru

437
00:27:34.960 --> 00:27:37.410
Let's settle this here and now!

438
00:27:41.550 --> 00:27:44.720
I'll give you a taste of my trick sword!

439
00:27:46.080 --> 00:27:50.180
I'll devastate Mount Atama!

440
00:27:50.180 --> 00:27:53.810
This is the end of the Mount Atama Thieves.

441
00:28:00.740 --> 00:28:03.160
It's too late! The fire is spreading fast!

442
00:28:03.160 --> 00:28:05.830
There's no extinguishing it, Shutenmaru!

443
00:28:07.830 --> 00:28:10.450
That bastard Holdem!

444
00:28:10.450 --> 00:28:12.580
Head to Bakura Town!

445
00:28:12.580 --> 00:28:16.750
Bakura Town?! We'll have
to contend with Kaido's forces!

446
00:28:16.750 --> 00:28:18.840
So what?!

447
00:28:19.460 --> 00:28:22.630
I'll crush them all!

448
00:28:24.560 --> 00:28:28.220
An Abandoned
Village in Kuri

449
00:28:28.220 --> 00:28:33.190
I see. I feel sorry for what is
happening to Ashura Doji.

450
00:28:33.190 --> 00:28:36.230
Mm-hm... But we did it for the greater good.

451
00:28:37.210 --> 00:28:38.650
It was unavoidable.

452
00:28:39.350 --> 00:28:40.940
We'll head to Bakura Town.

453
00:28:42.240 --> 00:28:46.320
Our plan was foiled,
and we have no solution in sight.

454
00:28:47.010 --> 00:28:51.830
For now, we'll get Ashura to see
the Beast Pirates as his enemy.

455
00:28:51.830 --> 00:28:56.540
His joining us is crucial to our cause!

456
00:28:56.540 --> 00:29:01.760
Ringo's
Northern
Cemetery

457
00:29:02.300 --> 00:29:04.470
Here I am... Wh-Wh-What?!

458
00:29:04.470 --> 00:29:06.890
What?!

459
00:29:11.470 --> 00:29:14.430
Who is this?! What is this?!

460
00:29:14.430 --> 00:29:16.850
Wh-Wh-What's the story here?!

461
00:29:17.880 --> 00:29:23.280
Brook? What's wrong with you?
Why are you here? Hm?

462
00:29:24.110 --> 00:29:28.600
Zoro, my eyes are popping
out of my skull just seeing you like that!

463
00:29:28.600 --> 00:29:32.310
I'm a skeleton, though,
so having eyes isn't really my thing!

464
00:29:33.440 --> 00:29:36.670
So sorry for the interruption!

465
00:29:37.510 --> 00:29:40.490
Hey, don't get the wrong idea!
Get back in here!

466
00:29:40.490 --> 00:29:44.470
Oh? Well, okay... If it's
no trouble, I'd be happy to.

467
00:29:46.430 --> 00:29:48.590
Wow, I'm smitten!

468
00:29:48.590 --> 00:29:53.520
If you would be so obliged,
may I see your panties?

469
00:30:00.730 --> 00:30:03.610
A ghost!

470
00:30:03.610 --> 00:30:06.110
Wait, he's with me!

471
00:30:08.530 --> 00:30:12.790
I'm so hungry... A curse on you!

472
00:30:14.230 --> 00:30:16.210
How scary!

473
00:30:16.910 --> 00:30:21.710
Kin'emon tasked me with
saying that around here.

474
00:30:21.710 --> 00:30:23.340
Oh, I see.

475
00:30:23.340 --> 00:30:26.800
That's why there are
so many offerings out there.

476
00:30:26.800 --> 00:30:31.520
At any rate, it's hard to believe
you're Momonosuke's little sister.

477
00:30:31.520 --> 00:30:35.980
You're as beautiful as an oiran.

478
00:30:36.670 --> 00:30:38.600
She sure is. I mean, she is an oiran.

479
00:30:38.600 --> 00:30:43.570
I'm jealous, Zoro. How'd you get
someone like this to tend to you?!

480
00:30:43.570 --> 00:30:46.820
I just went to sleep. That's all.

481
00:30:46.820 --> 00:30:51.410
I am so sorry. You just
looked like you were cold.

482
00:30:51.410 --> 00:30:56.740
Truth be told, everyone gets
love-struck lying next to me!

483
00:30:56.740 --> 00:31:00.600
Did you like it? No, certainly you loved it!

484
00:31:00.600 --> 00:31:03.590
Awful straightforward of you...!

485
00:31:02.600 --> 00:31:03.590
Of course!

486
00:31:03.590 --> 00:31:08.050
Anyway, I have no idea where
Nami and the others went.

487
00:31:08.050 --> 00:31:10.390
Yesterday, they went to the bathhouse,

488
00:31:10.390 --> 00:31:14.010
but they weren't there
when I went to meet them.

489
00:31:14.010 --> 00:31:18.350
Oh, that reminds me. The Flower Capital
is in an absolute frenzy.

490
00:31:19.140 --> 00:31:25.270
I heard that today is the funeral for
Komurasaki, Wano's most beautiful oiran.

491
00:31:26.650 --> 00:31:32.490
Plus, they caught the Witching Hour Boy,
the master thief who shared his spoils with the poor!

492
00:31:32.490 --> 00:31:34.160
That news is causing a fuss too!

493
00:31:34.160 --> 00:31:36.580
Ther Witching Hour Boy?!
But he couldn't have!

494
00:31:36.580 --> 00:31:38.750
But it's true.

495
00:31:38.750 --> 00:31:41.330
Look, it's right here on this broadsheet.

496
00:31:41.330 --> 00:31:46.550
It says that he will be executed in the capital today.
They even discovered his true identity.

497
00:31:41.330 --> 00:31:41.370
The Witching Hour
Boy Arrested

498
00:31:41.370 --> 00:31:41.420
The Witching Hour
